"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0729-1462448-paris-2024-irish-in-action-on-day-4-of-olympic-games\", \"text\": \"All Irish eyes will be on the exploits of world champion Daniel Wiffen in the pool just after 8pm, with the 23-year-old the hot favourite to land gold in the 800m freestyle final.  Wiffen, who won both the 800m and the 1500m at the World Championships in Doha earlier this, advanced to the biggest race of his life in 7:41.53 and was the fastest qualifier.  Defending champion Bobby Finke of the USA, Tunisian teenager Ahmed Jaouadi, Italy's Gregorio Paltrinieri and Elijah Winnington - who Wiffen accounted for in the heats - are the other realistic contenders for gold.  Early birds can tune in to RT\\u00c92 for coverage of the men's triathlon from 6.55am, with rowers Zoe Hyde and Alison Bergin the first Irish in action from around 9.50am.  Former taekwondo star Jennifer Lehane fights in boxing's bantamweight division at 11.36am, while the afternoon action sees Ireland pitted against India in men's hockey, Abigail Lyle and her mount Giraldo feature in individual dressage, Noel Hendrick and Michaela Corcoran take to the canoe course, Robert Dickson and Sean Waddilove continue their skiff race in sailing and Rachael Darragh will be on court in badminton.  You can follow the Olympic Games action all day with our live tracker on RT\\u00c9 Sport Online and the RT\\u00c9 News app, watch live from 6.55am on RT\\u00c92 and RT\\u00c9 Player, and listen to updates on RT\\u00c9 Radio 1 and 2fm.  (In order of start time)  0950-1010Women's double sculls semi-finals:Zoe Hyde and Alison Bergin  1010-1030Men's double sculls semi-finals:Philip Doyle and Daire Lynch  1030-1040Women's four repechage:Emily Hegarty, Natalie Long, Eimear Lambe and Imogen Magner  1136Women's 54kg (bantamweight) round of 16:Jennifer Lehanev Yuan Chang (Chn)  1215Men's Pool B:Irelandv India  1238Individual dressage qualifying Group B:Abigail Lyle (Giraldo)  1400-1455Women's C1 heats run 1 (third of 16 competitors):Michaela Corcoran  1500-1600Men's K1 heats run 1 (eighth of 16 competitors):Noel Hendrick  1610-1705Women's C1 heats run 2:Michaela Corcoran  1710-1810Men's K1 heats run 2:Noel Hendrick  1400Places 5-8: France vIreland  1700/1730Places 5-8:Irelandv China/Great Britain  1530-1610Skiff race 7:Robert Dickson and Sean Waddilove  1622-1702Skiff race 8:Robert Dickson and Sean Waddilove  1714-1754Skiff race 9:Robert Dickson and Sean Waddilove  1540 (or later)Group LRachael Darraghv Jenjira Stadelmann (Swi)  2002-2015Men's 800m freestyle final:Daniel Wiffen  Watch the 2024 Olympic Games with 14 hours of televised action on RT\\u00c92 and RT\\u00c9 Player each day. Listen to extensive radio coverage on RT\\u00c9 Radio 1 and 2fm's Game On and follow each moment from Paris on RT\\u00c9.ie, the RT\\u00c9 News app and all RT\\u00c9 digital platforms. Listen to the daily RT\\u00c9 Sport Olympics Podcast.    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"